args:
The vampire girl Vania appears at the Halidom
and urges the prince to become her bloodkin.
At her side is Chronos, an enemy of the prince,
but Vania claims that he is her friend Malinda.
Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor the Fractured Futures event.
Child born of the rift 'twixt fates, inheritor\nof altered life. Blood-sworn yet bloodless,\nmutation in causality's design...
The hour is come to slip your bonds of\nsilent slumber. Shed now those dreamless\ndepths and rise!
...Hm? Strange. I thought for a moment\nI heard someone speaking.
Heh. You are awake, transfigured prince.
You've naught to fear. I am not your foe. I\nam come on orders from the keeper of fate\nand causality, as a proud and biting wind.

I am the storming gale swept in from
beyond the clasp of cause and effect in
times of strife: the god of war. I am Griii...
Huh?
Wait, WHAT?! Out of time? Already?!\nNo, nonono... Ahhh, I haven't gotten to\nany of the important stuff yet! Oh jeez...
Uhhh, okay! I'm gonna need you to listen\nREAL well because I don't have time to\nrepeat myself. Soon, you'll meet a—
Huh? Er, yes I am.\nI don't think we've had the pleasure.
What brings you to the Halidom, Vania?
Well, you SEE... I've decided to make you\nmy bloodkin!
Bloodkin are super special people who do\nanything I ask them to!
So a servant, then? And I would\nagree to this...why, exactly?
Oh, because it's a HUGE honor!\nI'm jealous of how lucky you are, really.
Er, right... I'm afraid I don't quite follow,\nbut I'll have to ask that we continue this\nlittle game another time. I'm—
It's not a game! Assembling a large family\nof bloodkin is super important to vampires!
A creature of legends, said\nto feed on the blood of the living.
They supposedly possess tremendous\nstrength and magical ability, though their\ndiets lead some to label them as fiends.
And you claim to be one, miss?
Yup. I'm low-key a pretty big deal,\neven among vampires.
Okay, kiddo. That's enough make-believe\nfor today. You can come play again an—
I already TOLD you people it's not a game!\nGOSH, you're rude.
Vania has spoken true.\nShe is indeed a vampire.
So I say to you once more, my liege:\nI have come to see your wish realized.
All gathered here have come to twist time\nto their own ends.
Now, my liege! Now is the hour where\nI will finally see your wish realized!
You are but a vessel for my true liege,\nand for the sake of his glory, I will put\nyou to rest!
A foolish decision. But so be it.
Prepare yourself, vessel, for I shall scatter\nyou across the very winds of time!
Chronos?! Holy smokes! You don't mean...
The dragon who came to this world from\nthe future to manipulate time itself.
I had thought we defeated him then... But\nhis power is a serious threat. We cannot\nallow him to hatch some fresh plot now!
HEY! Why are you picking on poor\nMalinda?! She's my bestie and I\nwon't let you bully her.
And stop calling her a crone. She's young\nand gorgeous and you're just jealous.
YES! That's what I've been saying.\nIsn't it the cutest name? I gave it to her!
I know not who this ＂Chronos＂ is, but I am\ncalled...Malinda. I serve my liege, Vania.
(The voice, the manner of speaking...\nIt all screams Chronos, but...)
There. You tell 'em, Malinda. And tell\nthem what an amazing vampire I am\nwhile you're at it.
Of course. My liege is scion to a long and\nnoble line of vampires.
See? Everybody on the same page now?
Her fangs and the wings sprouting from\nher head DO align with traditional\ndescriptions. And yet...
I'm right there with you. Havin' some kid\nwaltz up and claim to be a legend's a\nlittle sus.
AUGH! If you're going to keep being this\nstubborn, I'm giving you all the chomp!
All right, all right. We believe you.
Great. So you're ready to become my\nbloodkin, then?
That's rather a different matter entirely...
Whaaat? Oh, c'mon. It'll be awesome!
I am sorry, but I have much that I still need\nto do.
I fear I cannot devote myself solely to you.
Aw, forget whatever other junk you've got\non the docket. If I say you're becoming my\nbloodkin, you're becoming my bloodkin!
And when I say that I cannot, I cannot.
LA LA LA, I CAN'T HEAR YOOOU! Look,\nI'm not leaving this place until you agree!
